magpie.data.utilities.generators

Class PrototypeEntryGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.generators.BaseEntryGenerator
      • magpie.data.utilities.generators.PrototypeEntryGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<BaseEntry>, Options

    public class PrototypeEntryGenerator
extends BaseEntryGenerator
    Generate PrototypeEntry with certain elements (or combination of elements on each site).

    Usage: <site info> -site <order> <spacing> <elements...> [-site <...>]
    site info: Path to file describing site information
    order: Maximum number of elements mixing on A site (≥ 1)
    spacing: Spacing (in at%) between mixed composition on each site. Example, 50 will generate A, AB, and B.
    elements: List of elements, by abbreviation that could exist on each site.
    Note: You must define the "-site" information for each site in the prototype in the order they are listed in the "site info" file.

    See Also:
    PrototypeDataset
